Over the last 18 months, WebSound have made huge progress in the Game and Web Hosting industry, supplying quality services at affordable prices. As part of our commitment to meeting our clients needs, we have listened to recent feedback and have decided to launch a new range of VPS services. We're pleased to announce the launch of our public beta for an upcoming VPS product, and would like to invite the community at LowEndTalk to participate. This beta test will allow us to put our upcoming services through a testing period, in which the service is used in a real time environment. The beta will allow us to monitor hardware and resources, gather feedback and also make final changes and amendments to our systems, ready for the official launch of this line of services next month.

We have 3 different packages on offer for the beta period, we're looking for around 10 different people per package to test them, allowing the users to make suggestions for improvements over the course of the next few weeks. Those who participate will get a month of free beta service, and will receive a 50% discount on the normal price if they decide to renew after the beta period, or, beta participants can simply cancel their service after the free month, should they wish to.

WebSound aim to fully launch these services on Monday 6th April 2015, with the free beta lasting for one month from the date that the order is placed.

